lksc 005 quickstart classroom page 1 for help call 650 724 7370 lksc classroom quick start guide lksc 005 1 choose your lighting lighting is controlled on the wall panel near the door which will dim the lights or switch them on or off for the front and or back of the room 2 choose your operating system windows is selected by default but if the computer is showing a mac screen click the apple icon in the top left corner and choose restart from the menu if the computer is off turn it on and it will boot into windows if you want to use mac os and the computer is showing a windows screen click the up arrow in the lower right corner then click the black diamond choose restart in mac os x if the computer is off turn it on and hold down the alt button to be presented with a choice of operating systems 3 select your source tap presentation on the touch panel top left and choose from four inputs left side lectern computer lectern dvi lectern vga and dvd the dvd player can found in the opposite corner of the room in the technology rack 4 select your destination and audio choose your display destination from the list on the presentation page one wall opposite lectern two wall near lectern you can send any of the sources to any of the two destinations or the same source to both by simply tapping the source and then the destination 5 turn the system off to turn the system off press the red circle next to the school of medicine logo in the upper left corner of the screen press yes to confirm when asked if you would like to power the system down
